<h4><a name="cat1-q1"></a>How does the Kiindly Social Match work?</h4>
<p>The Kiindly Social Match is a giving multiplier that increases your donation, and others before you, by either a dollar or penny increment.</p>
<p>For example, when joining a dollar match campaign, you are pledging to increase your donation by one dollar for every person that donates after you.  Your final donation amount will be determined as follows: the total number of unique donors at the end of the campaign multiplied by one dollar for each donor. For example, if there are 500 donors at the end of a campaign, your donation amount will be $500. If the total number of donors exceeds your maximum pledge amount, your final donation will be the maximum pledge amount. For example, if you selected a $20 maximum and 500 people donate, your donation will remain at the $20 limit you selected.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q2"></a>If the campaign does not reach my donation cap, can I still donate the full amount?</h4>
<p>Yes, you can! Just make sure check the box stating "If the campaign doesn't reach my donation cap I'm willing to donate the value of my full cap amount."</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q3"></a>Is my donation tax deductible?</h4>
<p>You should consult with your tax advisor on all contributions you make. Many organizations who use the Kiindly service are non profit organizations. We will provide you with a receipt for each donation you make that you may use for your tax records should the donation qualify as tax deductible.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q4"></a>Am I charged one dollar (or penny) at a time?</h4>
<p>No, we process all donations at the end of the campaign. When you first enter your credit card, we do validate the card but we don't process your final contribution until the end of the campaign.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q5"></a>When do I get charged?</h4>
<p>Within 7 days after the end of the campaign, we will process your credit card and send you a receipt. Once you complete your pledge, you will receive a confirmation email which contains the end date of the campaign.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q7"></a>Can I make multiple donations to increase the amount per donor?</h4>
<p>No. While this is a creative idea, it does not match the spirit of the social match provided by Kiindly. As a result, we only count donors as unique donors which means if you make multiple donations, you will be charged for all of your donations, but you will only be counted once in calculating the number of donors for the penny pledge calculation.</p>


